{"author":{"id":"4427f990a72b3f8829f36d619ccc38a02c473e37fa6ddc38986244869115373b"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1737936264,"nonce":"svGGwAwyNnAs8dhtjRJCMafD8zc=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOFkKpfs6b2E5O","github-url":"https://github.com/diegov/tabreport/issues/42#issuecomment-2614644302"},"message":"A possible explanation for this failing on FF versions that were working before, is that the FF errors were always happening, but Mozilla might have rebuilt and republished all FF builds with MOZ_CRASHREPORTER_SHUTDOWN set to true, and since we download the FF build from the server during each build, we're getting a different build now.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1765723745,"nonce":"A2GmP/qBDE9AYLX6ECfinuwvw/A=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOFkKpfs7ZonHZ","github-url":"https://github.com/diegov/tabreport/issues/42#issuecomment-3651301849"},"message":"It does seem to be a change in the FF dev builds, stable firefox doesn't crash. The\n`No canonical URL set up`  error is still there, although the `ActivityStreamPrefs.sys.mjs`\nerror is not. But no mention of MOZ_CRASHREPORTER_SHUTDOWN and no shutdown after the error.\n\nThe tests still fail on stable FF because it ignores `xpinstall.signatures.required`, so we\ncan't install the extension, but the immediate shutdown issue is specitic to the dev FF\nbuilds.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1765723745,"nonce":"mmopS0xrMWWdtaJhCEgjrKPElUM=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOFkKpfs7ZonHl","github-url":"https://github.com/diegov/tabreport/issues/42#issuecomment-3651301861"},"message":"This is probably related to the FF auto-update logic, which is now enabled in dev builds.\nThat's why disabling the action cache fixes the issue. The first run of FF uses the downloaded\nversion, then autoupdates, corrupting the cache in the process (maybe because we shut down the\ncontainer before the update is fully installed.)\n\nThe next run uses a corrupted FF installation from the action cache, and it fails.","files":null}